\par \pard\plain \li120\sb80\sl-240 \f8\fs20\lang1033 {\f4 WinVN is distributed via anonymous FTP from the hosts  }{\f7 titan.ksc.nasa.gov}{\f4   and  }{\f7 ripem.msu.edu}{\f4 .  The definitive version is always on  }{\f7 titan}{\f4 
.  Copies of WinVN can often be found at other sites, but they are sometimes badly out-of-date.  (The  }{\f7 ripem}{\f4   site  tends to lag behind  }{\f7 t}{\f7 itan}{\f4   by a day or so.)}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
Both source code and binaries for various platforms are distributed.  Sam Rushing's implementation of a generalized Winsock DLL has reduced the previous need to have a number of different versions of WinVN, one for each vendor's networking product.  Howev
}{\f4 er, WinVN can still be compiled for several different targets, including Windows NT on Intel and Alpha AXP machines.  Distributions are in the form of }{\f7 .ZIP}{\f4  files; be sure to use binary mode FTP to do the transfer.}{\f4 
